g.text: A slotted rest variable used in <Atom>s, <Expr>s and <Plex>s. Note
that <Plex>s are generated, so <resl>s are only...
an extension point for specializations of the slotted rest tag name. Stripe-skipping is
an extension point for specializations of the slot tag name.
In expressions, zero or more slots are allowed.
Slotted rest arguments follow the ordinary slots
in expressions in the normal-form serialization.
